A × B = {(1, x), (1, y), (2, x), (2, y), (3, x), (3, y)}
B × A = {(x, 1), (x, 2), (x, 3), (y, 1), (y, 2), (y, 3)}

As we can see, the ordered pairs in A × B and B × A are not the same. The first elements in the ordered pairs of A × B come from set A, while the first elements in the ordered pairs of B × A come from set B. Therefore, A × B and B × A are not equal.
